Randy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=inkspot@polykarbonbbs>inkspot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 4:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can anyone do calligraphy?</span><hr size=1> i can do it.i had to learn it when at school . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=randysilverman>Randy Silverman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 12:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can anyone do calligraphy?</span><hr size=1> That's wonderful. I have an assignment for a logo that involves the word &quot;nagare&quot; which means (I believe) &quot;to flow&quot; or &quot;flowing&quot; that uses the calligraphic version. The address to mail it to is &quot;rsilve1060@yahoo.com&quot;.<br>
<br>
BTW, I am very curious about your post. You write that you &quot;had&quot; to learn it in school. Did you go to school in Japan? It's really interesting that any other school would require that curriculum.<br>
<br>
Anyway, thank you very much for your help in this matter.<br>
<br>
Randy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=inkspot@polykarbonbbs>inkspot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/1/02 2:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can anyone do calligraphy?</span><hr size=1> Yes i was born in Hakone,Japan .I came to Australia to study at RMIT University.so about this calligraphy there are numbers ways one can do this do you want it to run down page cross page or something differnt do you want it in colour or black and white or what size do you want it more info would be great <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=randysilverman>Randy Silverman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/1/02 9:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Calligraphy</span><hr size=1> I was picturing a horizontal layout that's 3 - 4 inches in width (height would be proportional to whatever specs you determine). Solid black will be fine and, if you can, scan it at 600 dpi (cropped to, say, 1/16th inch from edges of artwork to minimize file size) and save it as a BITMAP, not grayscale, .tif file. It should send fine as is, but if for some reason it won't send, then you can down-res it to 300 dpi (it should still maintain it's form, shape, curves and lines without becoming bitmapped and jaggy).<br>
<br>
What are you studying at RMIT University? I'm wondering what RMIT stands for and it must have a good curriculum to draw students from Japan. As a guess, it sounds like Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology or something.<br>
<br>
Again, thank you for your time<br>
<br>
Randy Silverman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=inkspot@polykarbonbbs>inkspot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/4/02 7:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webspawner.com/users/lowbca/Inkspot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Calligraphy</span><hr size=1> Hi Again<br>
